## Validation Rules

### Email Validation
```dart
String? emailValidator(String? email) {
  if (email?.isNotEmpty ?? false) {
    if (_isEmailValid(email)) {
      return null; // Valid
    } else {
      return 'Please enter a valid email address';
    }
  } else {
    return 'Please enter your email address';
  }
}
```

### Password Validation
Strong password requirements:
- At least 8 characters
- At least one lowercase letter
- At least one uppercase letter
- At least one number
- At least one symbol
- No leading whitespace

```dart
String? passwordValidator(String? password) {
  if (password == null || password.isEmpty) {
    return 'Please enter your password';
  }
  if (password.startsWith(' ')) {
    return 'No leading white spaces allowed.';
  }
  if (password.length < 8) {
    return 'Password must be at least 8 characters long';
  }
  // Additional validation rules...
}
```

### Phone Validation
```dart
String? phoneValidator(String? value, int phoneLength) {
  RegExp regExp = RegExp(r'^[+]*[(]?[0-9]{1,4}[)]?[-\s./0-9]*$');
  bool isMatched = value != null ? regExp.hasMatch(value) : false;
  
  if (value == null || value.isEmpty) {
    return 'Please enter your mobile number';
  } else if (value.length < phoneLength) {
    return 'Please enter a valid mobile number';
  } else if (isMatched) {
    return null; // Valid
  } else {
    return 'Please enter a valid mobile number';
  }
}
```

## Form State Management

### Loading States
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  RxBool isSubmitting = false.obs;
  
  Future<void> onSubmit() async {
    if (formKey.currentState?.validate() ?? false) {
      isSubmitting(true);
      
      try {
        await _submitForm();
      } finally {
        isSubmitting(false);
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Error States
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  RxString formError = ''.obs;
  
  Future<void> onSubmit() async {
    formError.value = ''; // Clear previous errors
    
    if (formKey.currentState?.validate() ?? false) {
      final result = await _submitForm();
      
      result.when(
        (success) {
          // Handle success
        },
        (error) {
          formError.value = error;
        },
      );
    }
  }
}
```

### Real-time Validation
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  RxString emailError = ''.obs;
  
  void onEmailChanged(String value) {
    // Clear error when user starts typing
    if (emailError.value.isNotEmpty) {
      emailError.value = '';
    }
    
    // Optional: Real-time validation
    if (value.isNotEmpty && !_isEmailValid(value)) {
      emailError.value = 'Invalid email format';
    }
  }
}
```

## Custom Validators

### Creating Custom Validators
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  // Custom validator for specific requirements
  String? customValidator(String? value) {
    if (value == null || value.isEmpty) {
      return 'This field is required';
    }
    
    if (value.length < 3) {
      return 'Must be at least 3 characters';
    }
    
    if (!value.contains('@')) {
      return 'Must contain @ symbol';
    }
    
    return null; // Valid
  }
  
  // Conditional validator
  String? conditionalValidator(String? value) {
    if (someCondition && (value == null || value.isEmpty)) {
      return 'This field is required when condition is met';
    }
    return null;
  }
}
```

### Cross-field Validation
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  String? confirmPasswordValidator(String? value) {
    if (value != passwordController.text) {
      return 'Passwords do not match';
    }
    return null;
  }
  
  String? dateRangeValidator(String? value) {
    final startDate = DateTime.tryParse(startDateController.text);
    final endDate = DateTime.tryParse(value ?? '');
    
    if (startDate != null && endDate != null && endDate.isBefore(startDate)) {
      return 'End date must be after start date';
    }
    
    return null;
  }
}
```

## Form Submission Patterns

### Basic Submission
```dart
Future<void> onSubmit() async {
  if (formKey.currentState?.validate() ?? false) {
    FocusManager.instance.primaryFocus?.unfocus();
    
    final formData = {
      'name': nameController.text.trim(),
      'email': emailController.text.trim(),
      'phone': phoneController.text.trim(),
    };
    
    await _submitForm(formData);
  }
}
```

### With Loading State
```dart
Future<void> onSubmit() async {
  if (formKey.currentState?.validate() ?? false) {
    isLoading(true);
    
    try {
      final result = await _repository.submitForm(formData);
      
      result.when(
        (success) {
          AppSnackBar.success(message: 'Form submitted successfully');
          Get.back();
        },
        (error) {
          AppSnackBar.error(message: error);
        },
      );
    } finally {
      isLoading(false);
    }
  }
}
```

### With Confirmation
```dart
Future<void> onSubmit() async {
  if (formKey.currentState?.validate() ?? false) {
    final confirmed = await Get.dialog<bool>(
      AlertDialog(
        title: Text('Confirm Submission'),
        content: Text('Are you sure you want to submit this form?'),
        actions: [
          TextButton(
            onPressed: () => Get.back(result: false),
            child: Text('Cancel'),
          ),
          ElevatedButton(
            onPressed: () => Get.back(result: true),
            child: Text('Submit'),
          ),
        ],
      ),
    );
    
    if (confirmed == true) {
      await _submitForm();
    }
  }
}
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Form Validation
- Always validate on both client and server side
- Provide clear, actionable error messages
- Validate in real-time when appropriate
- Use appropriate keyboard types

### 2. User Experience
- Clear form labels and hints
- Show validation errors immediately
- Provide loading states during submission
- Handle form reset and cleanup

### 3. Performance
- Dispose text controllers properly
- Avoid unnecessary rebuilds
- Use debouncing for real-time validation
- Optimize form state management

### 4. Accessibility
- Use semantic labels
- Provide proper focus management
- Support screen readers
- Ensure proper contrast ratios

### 5. Security
- Sanitize input data
- Validate on server side
- Handle sensitive data carefully
- Use secure input methods for passwords